{"word":"ἁπλόος","slug":"ἁπλόος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἁπλόος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:ἅμα'><el>ἅμα</el></a> as <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>simplex</el> from <i>simul</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <a href='S:διπλόος'><el>διπλόος</el></a>, <i>duplex, twofold.</i>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>single</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>simple, natural, plain, sincere, frank</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: in bad sense, <i>simple</i>, <b><a href='S:Isocrates'>Isocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>simple</i>, <a href='S:opposed to'>opp. to</a> <i>compound</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>ἁπλῆ δημοκρατία</el> <i>sheer</i> democracy, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>simple, absolutely true</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>IV. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <a href='S:ἁπλῶς'><el>ἁπλῶς</el></a>, <a href='S:vide'>v.</a> sub <a href='S:voce, vocem'>voc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>V. </b><a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> and <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>ἁπλούστερος, ἁπλούστατος</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}